create an help style page like the manual for this commands with this arguments:

showArgs=-show -s /s
example: todo -s <starting_line> <limit_line> | todo -s --sect <section>

addArgs=-add -a /a
example: todo -a <entry> <section> | todo -a --sect <section>

removeArgs=-remove -rem -r -rm /r
example: todo -r <section> <index/indexes> | todo -r --sect <section>

tickArgs=-done -tick /t -t
example: todo -t <section> <index/indexes>

deleteArgs=-delete -del -d /d
example: todo -d <todo filename>

aliasArgs=-alias -al /al
example: todo -al <todo command> <alias>

settingsArgs=-settings -set /set -st -option -o /o -opt -icons -ico /i -i
example: todo -st | todo -st <setting_name> <setting_value>

The program is called "todo.bat" and it's purpose is to add a todo list to CMD. This list is divided in sections and each section as their entries enumerated with indexes starting from 1.